title: Readout of the President's Call with President Francois Hollande of France | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House
Office of the Press Secretary


For Immediate Release
November 13, 2015

 



Readout of the President's Call with President Francois Hollande of France





President Obama spoke by phone this morning with President Francois Hollande of France to discuss the upcoming Paris climate conference, which will begin on November 30.Â  Both leaders emphasized their personal commitment to reach an ambitious and durable climate change agreement as well as their determination to work together to do so. President Obama and President Hollande also previewed the upcoming G20 Summit in Antalya, Turkey, where they will meet in person this weekend.
